Tensions With Iran

Missile Photographs Fuel Divisions Over Iran Threat

  • The intelligence that caused the White House to escalate its warnings about Iran came from photographs of missiles on small boats, American officials said.
  • But how alarmed the Trump administration should be has been fiercely debated among the White House, the Pentagon, the C.I.A. and America’s allies.

Iraq, fearing another U.S. war, has warned militias tied to Iran against provocation.

Abortion Legislation

Supreme Court Could Change Abortion Rights Without the Alabama Law

  • The short-term threat to the constitutional right to abortion may not come from extreme measures like the one signed into law in Alabama on Wednesday.
  • The conservative majority may prefer to chip away at abortion rights rather than overturn Roe v. Wade outright. It will have plenty of chances to do so.

Trump Administration

Trump Immigration Proposal Emphasizes Immigrants’ Skills Over Family Ties

  • The plan, to be unveiled Thursday, would vastly scale back family-based immigration and increase education and skill requirements.
  • It is likely to be unpopular with lawmakers on both sides of the aisle. Officials conceded that it was a long way from becoming a legislative reality.

An executive order aimed to ban equipment that could pose a security threat. It would effectively block sales by Huawei, the Chinese tech giant.

Proposed New York Fur Ban Pits Animal Rights Advocates Against Black Ministers

  • A proposed ban on sales, similar to measures in Los Angeles and elsewhere, has a diverse set of opponents, including shop owners and Hasidic men.
  • Protesters outside City Hall on Wednesday yelled, “Put people first,” and counterprotesters answered, “How many animals have to die?”
586 comments

In India’s Elections, Women in the Running Need Men’s Blessings

  • This year, among the candidates that India’s political parties have fielded, only 8.8 percent have been women, according to an analysis.
  • It is a perplexing reality, as women in India have made it into leadership positions much earlier than in many Western democracies.
42 comments

‘Rabbit’ by Jeff Koons Smashes Record for Work by a Living Artist

  • The shiny stainless steel sculpture was purchased by Robert E. Mnuchin, the father of Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin, for $91.1 million with fees.
  • The sale topped the record at auction for a work by a living artist that was set just last November by David Hockney.
